title: Bug 114470[Smoke] Error message throws when using new Date("3/2/2005") as value in table filter.
description: Error message occurs when using new Date("3/2/2005") as a value in the table filter.
OB: Upon applying the table filter with the value new Date("3/2/2005"), an error message is displayed on the report page.
EB: When saving and previewing, the expected result is that the filter works without errors. However, the actual result shows errors on the report page, specifically in Table: table8. The error message is as follows: There are error(s) in Table: table8, Error0: data.engine.DataConversionError (1 time(s)), detail: An error occurred in data type conversion. Cannot convert it to Date. Cannot convert it to Date.
SR:
Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the application and navigate to the report page.
2. Apply a table filter with the value new Date("3/2/2005").
3. Save and preview the report.
4. Observe the errors on the report page.
